The paper deals with mathematical and computational properties of the nuclear norm for higher-order tensors, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and scientific computing (cs.SI). The paper discusses the complexity of computing the nuclear norm for tensors, which is a problem that is relevant to all of these subfields.
